# GOD MODE roadmap 2026-04-23 — P2-10 .netlifyignore.
#
# Mirrors .vercelignore so the Netlify build context (now live
# under the Faz 1 POC → Faz 3 cutover plan) receives the same
# deliberately-excluded-from-deploy files. Without this, Netlify
# uploaded every `.bundle` + port-workflow doc + sandbox shim on
# every build — ~40 MB of dead weight per deploy and unnecessary
# cold-read cost.
#
# Parity contract: every entry in .vercelignore must exist here
# (and vice versa). A pinned test enforces this so the two files
# cannot drift while both hosting targets are live during the
# cutover window.

# ---- port-workflow git bundles ----------------------------------
# The Flutter→Next port workflow tags every sprint and writes a
# `.bundle` file at repo root as an offline checkpoint. These are
# tracked in history but have zero runtime purpose; excluding them
# trims ~40 MB from every deploy.
*.bundle

# ---- historical tsconfig buildinfo backups ----------------------
# `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo.old*` are point-in-time backups of TypeScript's
# incremental build cache taken during the port. Not read by `tsc`,
# not referenced anywhere in the build.
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo.old*

# ---- sandbox tsconfig -------------------------------------------
# Local FUSE-mount workaround that remaps `@/generated/prisma` to a
# sandbox-generated Prisma client. Netlify runs `prisma generate` on
# its own during install, so this file is irrelevant to the build.
tsconfig.sandbox.json

# ---- internal port documentation --------------------------------
# Operator-facing, port-workflow specific docs. README.md, SETUP.md,
# DEPLOY.md, and MIGRATION_BASELINE.md are NOT excluded — they are
# the operator runbooks a fresh clone needs.
PORT_CHECKLIST.md
GIT_WORKFLOW.md

# ---- local .env files -------------------------------------------
# Defense in depth: `.env*` is already in `.gitignore`, but if a
# `.env.local` slips into the workspace it must never be uploaded.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
